HEADWORD: injured
<hw>injured</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>having received an
injury;-- usually used of physical or mental injury to persons. Opposite
of <ant>uninjured</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>abraded, scraped,
skinned </stype>; <stype>battle-scarred, scarred</stype>; <stype>bit,
bitten, stung </stype>; <stype>black-and-blue, livid </stype>;
<stype>bruised, contused, contusioned </stype>; <stype>bruised, hurt,
wounded </stype>; <stype>burned</stype>; <stype>cut, gashed, slashed,
split </stype>; <stype>disabled, hors de combat, out of action </stype>;
<stype>disjointed, dislocated, separated </stype>; <stype>hurt, wounded
</stype>; <stype>lacerated, mangled, torn</stype>; <stype>maimed,
mutilated </stype>] <see>Also See: <er>broken</er>, <er>damaged</er>,
<er>damaged</er>, <er>impaired</er>, <er>unsound</er>,
<er>wronged</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>subjected to an injustice.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> aggrieved.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

